GateDocument.TextWithNodes: CALL FOR PAPERS CALL FOR PAPERS CALL FOR PAPERS 3 rd International Workshop on Rules In Database Systems ( RIDS '97 ) June 26 - 28 , 1997 University of Skoevde , Sweden http : / / www . his . se / ida / ~ spiff / RIDS 97 / Scope - - - - - Following the success of RIDS- 93 ( 1 st International ) , and RIDS- 95 , the successor RIDS '97 will once again bring bring together researchers working on both theoretical and practical aspects of rules in database systems . Although extensive work has been carried out on supporting active rules and deductive rules in database systems , many questions are still open in order to turn these kinds of database systems into a practical technology . The RIDS '97 workshop intends to examine the current state of the art , to present novel and innovative approaches to rule systems , to discuss experiences with operational systems and real-life applications , and to identify future trends and developments . Suggested topics and issues include , but are not limited to : - application experiences - architectural issues and implementation experiences - deductive rules and integrity constraints - distribution aspects of rules - performance issues and tuning of active database systems - rule design , analysis , and simulation - rules for coordination , cooperation , and workflow management - rules in multi database environments - temporal aspects of rules - theoretical foundations of rules - tools ( debuggers , browsers , etc . ) Paper Submission - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Each submission should include original work not exceeding 20 double spaced pages or 5000 words . The cover page should include the title , name and affiliation of the author ( s ) , contact address , email , fax and telephone . Papers can be submitted as hard copies ( 5 copies ) to : RIDS '97 Andreas Geppert Institut fuer Informatik Universitaet Zuerich Winterthurerstr . 190 CH- 8057 Zuerich Switzerland Email : rids 97 @ aqs . fduxbr . hh Fax : + 41 - 1 - 363 0035 Ph . : + 41 - 1 - 257 4576 We also encourage electronic submissions , PROVIDED they consist of PostScript files that can be printed and ghostviewed under a Unix-like system . The Proceedings will be published as a volume of the Springer Lecture Notes in Computer Science series . Pre-proceedings will be distributed at the workshop . Workshop Format - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - Participation in the workshop will be limited to people actively contributing to the meeting .
